cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

The paper uses deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) to estimate urban greenery, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training the DCNNs, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses AI techniques to estimate urban greenery, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of self-driving car datasets, which suggests the involvement of robotics, falling under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves analyzing urban canopy cover, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
